WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:03.750
Alison, Al, time to wake up 

00:04.470 --> 00:06.340
Hi there doll face 

00:06.340 --> 00:07.900
You slept through the alarm.

00:07.900 --> 00:09.270
You doing okay?

00:09.300 --> 00:10.900
Middle of the night,you woke me up

00:10.930 --> 00:14.030
and told me you were feeling a little stiff.

00:14.120 --> 00:16.260
Why are you looking to me like that

00:16.260 --> 00:17.750
I don't know

00:17.750 --> 00:21.420
Things just seem different

00:21.420 --> 00:22.960
You seem different.

00:22.960 --> 00:24.140
Different?

00:24.140 --> 00:25.880
What do you mean different?

00:25.910 --> 00:27.580
Look at your face.

00:27.610 --> 00:29.510
Look at my arms!

00:29.540 --> 00:31.010
What are you talking about?

00:31.040 --> 00:32.380
Oh,my God!

00:32.409 --> 00:34.510
I think we're dolls!

00:34.540 --> 00:36.510
We're in the middle of a family crisis.

00:36.540 --> 00:38.410
I need everyone to pull together.

00:38.440 --> 00:39.640
What is it,Mom?

00:39.680 --> 00:40.780
What's the big deal?

00:40.780 --> 00:43.540
Honey,I really think
you're overreacting here.

00:43.580 --> 00:44.910
Overreacting?!

00:44.940 --> 00:46.840
We're dolls!

00:46.880 --> 00:48.480
All of us!

00:48.510 --> 00:51.510
Al,honestly,everything
is as it's always been.

00:51.540 --> 00:53.510
I have no idea what you're talking about.

00:53.540 --> 00:57.210
I'm talking about the fact
that you're six inches tall

00:57.240 --> 00:59.510
and your face is made of plastic!

00:59.540 --> 01:01.380
I'm talking about the fact

01:01.410 --> 01:04.540
that if I stripped off all
those doll clothes you're wearing

01:04.580 --> 01:06.440
I'd find a smooth little nub

01:06.480 --> 01:08.280
where your boy parts are supposed to be.

01:08.310 --> 01:10.480
Dad,what's wrong with Mom?

01:10.510 --> 01:11.810
She's just a little...

01:11.840 --> 01:12.940
Nothing!

01:12.980 --> 01:14.840
What is wrong with all of you?!

01:14.880 --> 01:16.640
You act like this is normal.

01:16.680 --> 01:19.340
We're human beings!

01:19.380 --> 01:21.140
We always have been!

01:21.180 --> 01:22.940
We dont live in a dollhouse!

01:22.980 --> 01:24.440
Shh!

01:24.480 --> 01:26.410
Mommy,you better be quiet.

01:26.440 --> 01:29.880
If you make too much noise,he'll hear you.

01:29.910 --> 01:31.180
What do you mean?

01:31.210 --> 01:32.380
Who'll hear me?

01:32.410 --> 01:33.980
Who's "he"?

01:34.010 --> 01:36.240
You know who "he" is.

01:39.110 --> 01:40.840
Ariel!

01:40.880 --> 01:43.510
Joe,we have to do something!

01:43.540 --> 01:44.510
Mommy!

01:44.540 --> 01:45.640
Bridgette!

01:45.680 --> 01:47.840
Joe!

01:47.880 --> 01:49.840
We have to hide,sweetie.

01:49.880 --> 01:50.840
No!

01:50.880 --> 01:52.910
Please!

01:52.940 --> 01:54.080
No,please!

01:54.110 --> 01:56.810
Don't hurt my family!

01:57.840 --> 02:00.140
Hey.

02:00.180 --> 02:03.280
You slept through the alarm.

02:03.310 --> 02:05.660
You doing okay?

02:05.660 --> 02:07.590
Middle of the night,you woke me up,

02:07.590 --> 02:11.240
told me you were feeling a little stiff.

02:11.280 --> 02:13.840
Why are you looking at me like that?

02:15.790 --> 02:16.310
You have,uh...

02:17.340 --> 02:19.080
toilet paper all over your face.

02:19.110 --> 02:20.940
I cut myself.

02:20.980 --> 02:22.410
We're all out of shaving cream.

02:22.440 --> 02:23.780
I was trying to make do.

02:23.810 --> 02:25.480
Ah,poor baby.

02:25.510 --> 02:26.740
I'll get you some.

02:26.780 --> 02:29.010
I was gonna go by the
drugstore this morning anyway.

02:29.040 --> 02:31.080
Thanks

02:31.110 --> 02:32.580
You're a doll.

